    </para>
    <para id="import-auto-id3149756">We are given information about the linear velocities of the motorcycle. Thus, we can find its linear acceleration <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>t</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{a rSub { size 8{t} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>. Then, the expression <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mi>α</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:msub><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>t</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mi>r</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{a rSub { size 8{t} } =rα,`````α= {  {a rSub { size 8{t} } }  over  {r} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> can be used to find the angular acceleration.</para>
